<br>
However, I don't think we can find any method at all that allows us to objectively state that Person A from a_small_guild_01 is more deserving thatn Person B from uber_guild_02.  After all, what if, immediately after getting their epic, Person A dumps a_small_guild_01 and moves on to uber_guild_02?  What's to keep people from leaving big guilds, joining a small guild to get their name high on the list, then going back to their original guild?<br>
<br>
Also, we shouldn't punish someone just because they belong to a guild with a few epic clerics.  The epic does have a use outside of raiding; a cleric that does the work should have their fair place on the list.<br>
<br>
My one and only hope is that there are no bots on the list.  That's the one thing I truly could not abide: that someone who's botted a cleric trying for an epic over someone who's actively playing a cleric.  The distinction may be fine, but very important to me at least.  You want to bot a cleric, fine, just don't try to make that cleric epic while this Ragefire spawn thing is so screwed up.  Let &quot;real&quot; clerics get it for now.<br>
<br>
Anyway, those are my two cents on the subject.  Since it would be impossible to judge who &quot;needs&quot; the epic more, the first-come first-served method is the best that can be devised.<br>
<br>
Now, if only I could find a way to get the SF zone to reset after every RF kill.... &lt;wistful sigh&gt;<br>
